<p>Viewing general status of a release</p><p>Quickly view the development status of a release, iteration, or
	 work package. 
  </p> 
	  
		<p> Using the CORDAP Dashboard, you
		  can view the status of your release, its iterations, and work packages. 
		</p> 
		<p>
		  
			 <p>During this task, if you need to go back up a level, use the
				breadcrumb trail within the 
				Status area. 
			 
		  </p>
		</p> 
		 
		   Select your product from the drop-down at the top of the
			 Dashboard tab. 
		   
		   
			 <p>The Dashboard is refreshed and
				shows status information for the selected product. 
			 </p> 
		   
		 
		  Place your cursor over the status bar to see the percentage of the
			 work completed.
		   
		   
			 <p>This step can be repeated when
				you view the status for iterations and work packages. 
			 </p> 
		   
		 
		  Click a release to show the status of the iterations within the
			 release. 
		   
		 
		 
		  Click an iteration to show the status of the work packages within
			 the iteration. 
		   
		  
			 <p>
				
				  <p>Clicking the name of the work package opens the work package
					 for editing.
				  </p>
				
			 </p>	 
		<p> The statuses are displayed. 
		</p> 
	  
  